  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2). The hemolysis transport model employs the Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law damage accumulation formulation, which is theoretically valid under the assumption that erythrocyte damage accumulates linearly with exposure time at a given shear-stress magnitude (linear superposition of sub-lethal stress events). Validation was performed at a single nominal operating point (5 L/min, 3000 RPM) where shear-stress histories are approximately monotonic and the linearity assumption is not materially challenged; however, the COU spans five flow-speed combinations that include low-flow/high-speed regimes in which recirculation zones produce highly non-monotonic, cyclically varying shear histories for which the linear superposition precondition may not hold.",
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cou1-hemolysis-rh-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cou1-cfd-identifies-worstcase-hemolysis",
  "bindsModel": "https://uofa.net/synth/model/morrison-cfd-giersiepen-wurzinger-hemolysis",
