      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "PIV velocity field comparison at nominal operating point (5 L/min, 3000 RPM)",
      "description": "Particle image velocimetry measurements acquired at the nominal CPB operating point were compared against CFD-predicted velocity fields. Mean absolute error in the impeller exit plane was 4.2% of tip velocity. This operating point features smoothly varying shear histories that are consistent with the linear superposition assumption of the Giersiepen-Wurzinger model; however, no validation activities were conducted at off-nominal flow-speed combinations where recirculation is pronounced.",
      "outcome": "Pass",
      "metricValue": 0.042,
      "metricUnit": "fractional MAE"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr02-hemolysis-index-nominal",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index prediction vs. in vitro measurement at nominal point",
      "description": "Predicted normalised index of hemolysis (NIH) compared against in vitro roller-pump reference at 5 L/min, 3000 RPM. Predicted NIH = 0.0031 mg/100 L; measured NIH = 0.0034 mg/100 L; relative error 8.8%, within the 15% acceptance band. Agreement at this single condition is used to assert model adequacy across all five COU operating points. The package contains no validation result addressing whether the linear damage-accumulation precondition holds at the four remaining operating points.",
      "outcome": "Pass",
      "metricValue": 0.088,
      "metricUnit": "fractional relative error"
    },
    {
