      "rationale": "In vitro PIV and hemolysis experiments conducted at 5.0 ± 0.1 L/min and 3000 ± 15 RPM, within the ±5% tolerance. Blood analogue fluid (glycerol-water, viscosity matched to whole blood at 37°C) used. Test conditions are representative of the nominal COU point."
