      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; analyst qualification records are sufficient.",
      "rationale": "Simulations executed by a CFD analyst with five years of cardiovascular pump experience. Peer review of boundary condition setup completed. Formal use-error assessment not required at MRL 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The selected turbulence closure and hemolysis transport model must be justified by published literature for blood pump CFD at the Reynolds numbers present in the COU.",
      "rationale": "SST k-omega turbulence closure selected based on published FDA pump benchmark studies demonstrating superior performance in rotating passage flows at Re ~ 10^4. Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law hemolysis model selected as the de-facto standard for pump hemolysis CFD per published literature. The model is theoretically predicated on the assumption that sub-lethal red cell damage accumulates linearly with shear-stress exposure time — i.e., that the damage integral is path-independent with respect to stress history ordering. This precondition is stated in the original Giersiepen et al. (1990) derivation and is acknowledged in the model narrative. Validation evidence at the nominal operating point is consistent with the assumption; however, no dedicated analysis or sensitivity study is included in this package to confirm that the precondition holds for the recirculation-dominated, cyclically varying shear histories present at the low-flow/high-speed COU points."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Inlet boundary conditions (flow rate, fluid properties) must be specified within ±5% of COU operating values; pump geometry must be as-designed nominal.",
      "rationale": "Inlet mass flow rates for all five operating points derived from clinical CPB flow specifications. Blood viscosity set to 0.0035 Pa·s (Newtonian approximation, appropriate for high-shear pump interior). Geometry imported from certified CAD file. All inputs traceable to source documents."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
